Noah Williamsin diving and Georgia Bell in the women's 1500 metres.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999981936817164, \"rank\": 1.7603157894568609e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}, {\"begin\": 638, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.7948322203849637, \"rank\": 0.24947676701091526, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB also claimed bronze medals in both men's and women's 4x400m relay events.\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9691664241728092, \"rank\": 0.03181453159974947, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, the PA news agency takes a look back at Saturday's action.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thorpe and Shortman won technical silver and free bronze at the World Aquatics Championships earlier this year so they came toParisahead of the women's duet in high spirits.\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"score\": 0.8397191147584429, \"rank\": 0.16325545063999225, \"text\": \"Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The events are combined in Paris and after a Big Ben-themed technical left them fourth, Thorpe and Shortman delivered a RisingPhoenixfree routine that was adjudged the best of the 17-strong field.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1031, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994814405889, \"rank\": 5.185596488267962e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"score\": 0.8397191147584429, \"rank\": 0.16325545063999225, \"text\": \"Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was enough to lift the childhood friends, whose mothers used to compete alongside one another, into silver in the women's duet for Team GB's first Olympic medal in artistic swimming.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9691664241728092, \"rank\": 0.03181453159974947, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cunningham had to settle for Olympic silver after being beaten by Iran's Arian Salimi in the final of the men's +80kg category in Paris.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1391, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999981936817164, \"rank\": 1.7603157894568609e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}, {\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998878088126444, \"rank\": 0.00011143913830508962, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999994814405889, \"rank\": 5.185596488267962e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old from Huddersfield won the first round 6-3 but was edged out in the next two as the Iranian pulled away to ensure his nation's third taekwondo gold.\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huddersfield_Town_A.F.C.\", \"score\": 0.8852314358056269, \"rank\": 0.11686549194941159, \"text\": \"Huddersfield\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huddersfield_Town_A.F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huddersfield_Town_A.F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\", \"score\": 0.9215091526628263, \"rank\": 0.04062899239200345, \"text\": \"Iranian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iranian_peoples\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cunningham's medal sealed a gutsy comeback from a serious knee injury in his opening bout at the 2022 World Championships in Mexico, which forced him out of action for a number of months.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"score\": 0.9999981936817164, \"rank\": 1.7603157894568609e-06, \"text\": \"Cunningham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Briggs_Cunningham\"}, {\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9927315356366779, \"rank\": 0.006343142709459734, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams scraped into the men's 10m platform final, sealing the 12th and last qualifying place, but looked set to miss out on the podium after dropping to fifth with two dives left.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 2064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the 24-year-old, who won silver with Tom Daley in the synchronised event earlier in the Games, delivered a brilliant response with excellent scores of 93.60 and 94.35.\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4345692966963386e-48, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coupled with his rivals slipping up, Williams got himself into the medal positions and said afterwards: \\\"I am pretty shocked, I did bad earlier.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not feel like I did not deserve to get into the final.\\\"\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the United States walked away with both gold medals in the 4x400m relays, Team GB can be happy after finishing third in both men's and women's events.\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9995375098712466, \"rank\": 0.00044177485575734956, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9691664241728092, \"rank\": 0.03181453159974947, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Haydock-Wilson led off for GB, and though individual men's 400m silver medallistMatthew Hudson-Smithfound himself locked into a battle for second, Britain remained third after his second lap.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2609, \"end\": 2613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999999999240572, \"rank\": 7.296425065033838e-11, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9363914476748657, \"rank\": 0.06787543301088059, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2761, \"end\": 2768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6041841775449672, \"rank\": 0.6551167558556074, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The USA extended their advantage, and by the time Lewis Davey handed off to Charlie Dobson and he rounded the final bend, there was considerable distance both in front of and behind the British anchor.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9429626717076759, \"rank\": 0.059986908657452036, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2857, \"end\": 2862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"score\": 0.999991613337368, \"rank\": 8.386717694267203e-06, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\"}, {\"begin\": 2863, \"end\": 2868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Davey\", \"score\": 0.7081297983716177, \"rank\": 0.41217048171776655, \"text\": \"Davey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Davey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Davey\"}, {\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9906214335452737, \"rank\": 0.009436947889732445, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\"}, {\"begin\": 2993, \"end\": 3000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.8812752520645025, \"rank\": 0.09425142227668432, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's 4x400m quartet of Victor